{
  "texts": [
    "Unlike traditional classifiers, the DNN architecture allows for learning intricate patterns and relationships within the data, enabling it to effectively distinguish between normal and extreme values.",
    "The DNN consists of multiple hidden layers, each containing a large number of neurons, which enables it to learn complex representations of the input data.",
    "By training on a diverse range of time series data containing normal and extreme values, the Extreme Value Classifier can accurately identify and classify extreme events (Fig. 4).",
    "Preparing forecastOutput of LSTM and Transformer model are denormalized and multiplied with output of classifiers in corresponding elements.",
    "These applied outputs are then combined with the summation of corresponding elements."
  ]
}